data <- read.csv("insurance_cost.csv", stringsAsFactors = TRUE)

# 

## 'data.frame':    1338 obs. of  7 variables:
##  $ age     : int  19 18 28 33 32 31 46 37 37 60 ...
##  $ sex     : Factor w/ 2 levels "female","male": 1 2 2 2 2 1 1 1 2 1 ...
##  $ bmi     : num  27.9 33.8 33 22.7 28.9 ...
##  $ children: int  0 1 3 0 0 0 1 3 2 0 ...
##  $ smoker  : Factor w/ 2 levels "no","yes": 2 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 1 ...
##  $ region  : Factor w/ 4 levels "northeast","northwest",..: 4 3 3 2 2 3 3 2 1 2 ...
##  $ charges : num  16885 1726 4449 21984 3867 ...

# charges. . . . . .

charges_mean <- round(mean(data$charges),1)
charges_median <- round(median(data$charges),1)

ggplot(data = data, 
       aes(x = charges)) +
  geom_density()+
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_mean), color = 'red') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = charges_mean+5000,
           y = 0.0001, 
           label=paste0("Mean=", charges_mean), color = 'blue', size = 3) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_median), color = 'green') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = charges_median-5000,
           y = 0.00001, 
           label=paste0("Median=", charges_median), color = 'brown', size = 3)+
  ggtitle('   ') + 
  labs(y = ' ', x = '  ') +
  theme(
    title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=10), axis.title.x = element_text(size=10) )

#- box_plot charges (1) sex (2) smoker (3) region. . .

  ggplot() +

    title = element_text(size = 10),

    ) +

  geom_density()+
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_mean), color = 'red') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = charges_mean+5000,
           y = 0.0001, 
           label=paste0("Mean=", charges_mean), color = 'blue', size = 3) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = charges_median), color = 'green') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = charges_median-5000,
           y = 0.00001,

  ggtitle('   ') + 
  labs(y = ' ', x = '  ') +
  theme(
    title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=10), axis.title.x = element_text(size=10) )+
  facet_grid(. ~ region) +
  theme_minimal()

# 14

data <- data %>% 
  mutate(
    log_charges = log(charges),
    age_group = case_when(
      age < 35 ~ "age: 21-34",
      age >= 35 & age < 50 ~ "age: 35-49",
      age >= 50 ~ "age: 50+"
    ))

data %>% 
  filter(bmi != 0 & log_charges != 0) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=bmi, y=log_charges, color = age_group, fill = age_group, group = age_group)) + 
    geom_point(size=1, color = '#660099', alpha = 0.4)+
  geom_smooth(method=lm,
             fullrange = T, fill="#69b3a2", alpha = 0.1, 
              se=TRUE)+
  facet_grid(. ~ age_group)+
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle('         ') +
  labs(y = 'log(charges)', x = 'bmi')+
  theme(title = element_text(size = 8), axis.text.x = element_text(size=8), axis.text.y = element_text(size=8), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 11), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 11), legend.position = 'bottom', legend.text = element_text(size = 8), legend.title = element_text(size = 10))
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

# 1 , 

data_fem <- data[data$sex == 'female', ]

bmi_mean <- round(mean(data_fem$bmi),1)
bmi_median <- round(median(data_fem$bmi),1)

ggplot(data = data_fem, 
       aes(x = bmi)) +
  geom_histogram(color = 'black', fill = 'white')+
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = bmi_mean), color = 'red') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = bmi_mean+5,
           y = 10, 
           label=paste0("Mean=", bmi_mean), color = 'blue', size = 5) +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = bmi_median), color = 'green') +
  annotate("text", 
           x = bmi_median-5,
           y = 45, 
           label=paste0("Median=", bmi_median), color = 'brown', size = 5)+
  ggtitle('   ') + 
  labs(y = ' ', x = '') +
  theme(
    title = element_text(size = 12),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size=10), axis.title.x = element_text(size=10) )

# 3 , ( <2), ( 35-49 2-4 >5)

data_fem <- data_fem %>% 
  mutate(
    children_group = case_when(
      children < 2 ~ "children: <2",
      children >= 2 & children < 5 ~ "children: 2-4",
      children >= 5 ~ "children: >5"
    ))

ggplot() +
  geom_bar(data = data_fem, 
           aes(x = age_group, fill = children_group), 
           position="dodge")+
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle('       ') +
  labs(y = '     ', x = ' ')+
  theme(title = element_text(size = 8), axis.text.x = element_text(size=8), axis.text.y = element_text(size=8), axis.title.x = element_text(size = 9), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 9), legend.position = 'bottom', legend.text = element_text(size = 8), legend.title = element_text(size = 10))
